Institutionalized
All human activity is subject to habitualization: the process of performing an act frequently enough that it becomes a pattern, an almost unconscious reflex.
Institutionalization occurs when habitualized actions are recognized and repeated by a number of actors.
History and control are central to institutions: the actions performed by actors have been done over time, and they ultimately control human actions via habits.
Once an act is institutionalized, you dont need any rules to get people to do it: the institution itself serves as the enforcing body.
